  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DEC Covid-19 Appeal Phase 1</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the project is to reach the most at-risk, conflict-affected communities with targeted food support and inclusive WASH assistance to mitigate the impacts of COVID-19 and combat the spread of the virus. Specifically, Concern is proposing an integrated COVID-19 emergency response in Khanabad district of Kunduz Province entailing:
  1) the installation of age, gender, and disability-inclusive handwashing stations at public gathering areas such as mosques and markets;
  2) the rehabilitation of damaged village hand pump wells that are safe and accessible to all vulnerability groups; 
 3) the distribution of the FSAC Cluster recommended one-month food basket via cash support; and 
 4) the implementation of inter-personal COVID-19 awareness raising campaigns, tailored to varying levels of literacy.</narrative>
  </description>
